Public broadcaster SABC has issued a public statement on one of the biggest radio stations Ukhozi FM. The station is said to have unscheduled three members of the breakfast show. The three members of the breakfast show who have been unscheduled on Ukhozi Fm are  Sipho ‘Mgqemeza’ Mbatha, who is the host, and two producers of the show. “Ukhozi FM management regrets to inform the station’s listeners that three members of the breakfast show team have been unscheduled following an internal investigation,” reads the statement. The statement said management will not discuss the matter further as it is an employer-employee relationship governed by the Corporation’s policies. Management has however put measures in place to ensure continuity of the show. Former Ukhozi FM presenter Siya Mhlongo is the stand-in Presenter who will co-host the show with Nonhlanhla ‘Mroza’ Buthelezi. Also Read: Former Ukhozi presenter Siya Mhlongo lands new job on Metro FM For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.